279  void updateChildren(DocumentObjectDataPtr other) {
280  children = other->children;

283 
284  bool updateChildren(bool checkVisibility) {
285  auto newChildren = viewObject->claimChildren();
286  auto obj = viewObject->getObject();
287  std::set<App::DocumentObject*> newSet;
288  bool updated = false;
289  for (auto child : newChildren) {
290  auto childVp = docItem->getViewProvider(child);
291  if (!childVp)
292  continue;
293  if (child && child->isAttachedToDocument()) {
294  if (!newSet.insert(child).second) {
295  TREE_WARN("duplicate child item " << obj->getFullName()
296  << '.' << child->getNameInDocument());
297  }
298  else if (!childSet.erase(child)) {
299  // this means new child detected
300  updated = true;
301  if (child->getDocument() == obj->getDocument() &&
302  child->getDocument() == docItem->document()->getDocument())
303  {
304  auto& parents = docItem->_ParentMap[child];
305  if (parents.insert(obj).second && child->Visibility.getValue()) {
306  bool showable = false;
307  for (auto parent : parents) {
308  if (!parent->hasChildElement()
309  && parent->getLinkedObject(false) == parent)
310  {
311  showable = true;
312  break;
313  }
314  }
315  childVp->setShowable(showable);
316  }
317  }
318  }
319  }
320  }
321  for (auto child : childSet) {
322  if (newSet.find(child) == newSet.end()) {
323  // this means old child removed
324  updated = true;
325  auto mapIt = docItem->_ParentMap.find(child);
326 
327  // If 'child' is not part of the map then it has already been deleted
328  // in _slotDeleteObject.
329  if (mapIt != docItem->_ParentMap.end()) {
330  docItem->_ParentMap[child].erase(obj);
331 
332  auto childVp = docItem->getViewProvider(child);
333  if (childVp && child->getDocument() == obj->getDocument())
334  childVp->setShowable(docItem->isObjectShowable(child));
335  }
336  }
337  }
338  // We still need to check the order of the children
339  updated = updated || children != newChildren;
340  children.swap(newChildren);
341  childSet.swap(newSet);
342 
343  if (updated && checkVisibility) {
344  for (auto child : children) {
345  auto childVp = docItem->getViewProvider(child);
346  if (childVp && child->getDocument() == obj->getDocument())
347  childVp->setShowable(docItem->isObjectShowable(child));
348  }
349  }
350  return updated;
351  }

381 class DocumentItem::ExpandInfo :
382  public std::unordered_map<std::string, DocumentItem::ExpandInfoPtr>
383 {
384 public:
385  void restore(Base::XMLReader& reader) {
386  int level = reader.level();
387  int count = reader.getAttributeAsInteger("count");
388  for (int i = 0; i < count; ++i) {
389  reader.readElement("Expand");
390  auto& entry = (*this)[reader.getAttribute("name")];
391  if (!reader.hasAttribute("count"))
392  continue;
393  entry.reset(new ExpandInfo);
394  entry->restore(reader);
395  }
396  reader.readEndElement("Expand", level - 1);
397  }
398 };

406 class TreeWidgetItemDelegate: public QStyledItemDelegate {
407  typedef QStyledItemDelegate inherited;
408 
409  // Beware, big scary hack incoming!
410  //
411  // This is artificial QTreeWidget that is not rendered and its sole goal is to be the source
412  // of style information that can be manipulated using QSS. From Qt6.5 tree branches also
413  // have rendered background using ::item sub-control. Whole row also gets background from
414  // the same sub-control. Only way to prevent this is to disable background of ::item,
415  // this however limits our ability to style tree items. As solution we create this widget
416  // that will be for painter to read information and draw proper backgrounds only when asked.
417  //
418  // More information: https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/13807
419  QTreeView *artificial;
420 
421  QRect calculateItemRect(const QStyleOptionViewItem &option) const;
422 
423 public:
424  explicit TreeWidgetItemDelegate(QObject* parent=nullptr);
425 
426  virtual QWidget* createEditor(QWidget *parent,
427  const QStyleOptionViewItem &, const QModelIndex &index) const;
428 
429  virtual QSize sizeHint(const QStyleOptionViewItem &option, const QModelIndex &index) const;
430 
431  virtual void initStyleOption(QStyleOptionViewItem *option, const QModelIndex &index) const;
432 
433  virtual void paint(QPainter *painter, const QStyleOptionViewItem &option, const QModelIndex &index) const;
434 };

447 QRect TreeWidgetItemDelegate::calculateItemRect(const QStyleOptionViewItem &option) const
448 {
449  auto tree = static_cast<TreeWidget*>(parent());
450  auto style = tree->style();
451 
452  QRect rect = option.rect;
453 
454  const int margin = style->pixelMetric(QStyle::PM_FocusFrameHMargin, &option, artificial) + 1;
455 
456  // 2 margin for text, 2 margin for decoration (icon) = 4 times margin
457  int width = 4 * margin
458  + option.fontMetrics.boundingRect(option.text).width()
459  + option.decorationSize.width()
460  + TreeParams::getItemBackgroundPadding()
461  ;
462 
463  if (TreeParams::getCheckBoxesSelection()) {
464  // another 2 margin for checkbox
465  width += 2 * margin
466  + style->pixelMetric(QStyle::PM_IndicatorWidth)
467  + style->pixelMetric(QStyle::PM_LayoutHorizontalSpacing);
468  }
469 
470  if (width < rect.width()) {
471  rect.setWidth(width);
472  }
473 
474  return rect;
475 }

477 void TreeWidgetItemDelegate::paint(QPainter *painter,
478  const QStyleOptionViewItem &option, const QModelIndex &index) const
479 {
480  QStyleOptionViewItem opt = option;
481  initStyleOption(&opt, index);
482 
483  auto tree = static_cast<TreeWidget*>(parent());
484  auto style = tree->style();
485 
486  // If only the first column is shown, we'll trim the color background when
487  // rendering as transparent overlay.
488  bool trimColumnSize = isOnlyNameColumnDisplayed();
489 
490  if (index.column() == 0) {
491  if (tree->testAttribute(Qt::WA_NoSystemBackground)
492  && (trimColumnSize || (opt.backgroundBrush.style() == Qt::NoBrush
493  && _TreeItemBackground.style() != Qt::NoBrush)))
494  {
495  QRect rect = calculateItemRect(option);
496 
497  if (trimColumnSize && opt.backgroundBrush.style() == Qt::NoBrush) {
498  painter->fillRect(rect, _TreeItemBackground);
499  } else if (!opt.state.testFlag(QStyle::State_Selected)) {
500  painter->fillRect(rect, _TreeItemBackground);
501  }
502  }
503  }
504  style->drawControl(QStyle::CE_ItemViewItem, &opt, painter, artificial);
505 }
506 
507 void TreeWidgetItemDelegate::initStyleOption(QStyleOptionViewItem *option,
508  const QModelIndex &index) const
509 {
510  inherited::initStyleOption(option, index);
511 
512  auto tree = static_cast<TreeWidget*>(parent());
513  auto item = tree->itemFromIndex(index);
514 
515  if (!item) {
516  return;
517  }
518 
519  auto mousePos = option->widget->mapFromGlobal(QCursor::pos());
520  auto isHovered = option->rect.contains(mousePos);
521  if (!isHovered) {
522  option->state &= ~QStyle::State_MouseOver;
523  }
524 
525  QSize size = option->icon.actualSize(QSize(0xffff, 0xffff));
526 
527  if (size.height() > 0) {
528  option->decorationSize = QSize(
529  size.width() * TreeWidget::iconSize() / size.height(),
530  TreeWidget::iconSize()
531  );
532  }
533 
534  if (isOnlyNameColumnDisplayed()) {
535  option->rect = calculateItemRect(*option);
536 
537  // we need to extend this shape a bit, 3px on each side
538  // this value was obtained experimentally
539  option->rect.setWidth(option->rect.width() + 3 * 2);
540  }
541 }

569 QWidget* TreeWidgetItemDelegate::createEditor(
570  QWidget *parent, const QStyleOptionViewItem &, const QModelIndex &index) const
571 {
572  auto ti = static_cast<QTreeWidgetItem*>(index.internalPointer());
573  if (ti->type() != TreeWidget::ObjectType || index.column() > 1)
574  return nullptr;
575  auto item = static_cast<DocumentObjectItem*>(ti);
576  App::DocumentObject* obj = item->object()->getObject();
577  auto& prop = index.column() ? obj->Label2 : obj->Label;
578 
579  std::ostringstream str;
580  str << "Change " << obj->getNameInDocument() << '.' << prop.getName();
581  App::GetApplication().setActiveTransaction(str.str().c_str());
582  FC_LOG("create editor transaction " << App::GetApplication().getActiveTransaction());
583 
584  DynamicQLineEdit *editor;
585  if(TreeParams::getLabelExpression()) {
586  DynamicQLineEdit *le = new DynamicQLineEdit(parent);
587  le->setAutoApply(true);
588  le->setFrame(false);
589  le->bind(App::ObjectIdentifier(prop));
590  editor = le;
591  } else {
592  editor = new DynamicQLineEdit(parent);
593  }
594  editor->setReadOnly(prop.isReadOnly());
595  return editor;
596 }

823  if (!searchObject)

837 void TreeWidget::startItemSearch(QLineEdit* edit) {
838  resetItemSearch();
839  searchDoc = nullptr;
840  searchContextDoc = nullptr;
841  auto sels = selectedItems();
842  if (sels.size() == 1) {
843  if (sels.front()->type() == DocumentType) {
844  searchDoc = static_cast<DocumentItem*>(sels.front())->document();
845  }
846  else if (sels.front()->type() == ObjectType) {
847  auto item = static_cast<DocumentObjectItem*>(sels.front());
848  searchDoc = item->object()->getDocument();
849  searchContextDoc = item->getOwnerDocument()->document();
850  }
851  }
852  else
853  searchDoc = Application::Instance->activeDocument();
854 
855  App::DocumentObject* obj = nullptr;
856  if (searchContextDoc && !searchContextDoc->getDocument()->getObjects().empty())
857  obj = searchContextDoc->getDocument()->getObjects().front();
858  else if (searchDoc && !searchDoc->getDocument()->getObjects().empty())
859  obj = searchDoc->getDocument()->getObjects().front();
860 
861  if (obj)
862  static_cast<ExpressionLineEdit*>(edit)->setDocumentObject(obj);
863 }

865 void TreeWidget::itemSearch(const QString& text, bool select) {
866  resetItemSearch();
867 
868  auto docItem = getDocumentItem(searchDoc);
869  if (!docItem) {
870  docItem = getDocumentItem(Application::Instance->activeDocument());
871  if (!docItem) {
872  FC_TRACE("item search no document");
873  resetItemSearch();
874  return;
875  }
876  }
877 
878  auto doc = docItem->document()->getDocument();
879  const auto& objs = doc->getObjects();
880  if (objs.empty()) {
881  FC_TRACE("item search no objects");
882  return;
883  }
884  std::string txt(text.toUtf8().constData());
885  try {
886  if (txt.empty())
887  return;
888  if (txt.find("<<") == std::string::npos) {
889  auto pos = txt.find('.');
890  if (pos == std::string::npos)
891  txt += '.';
892  else if (pos != txt.size() - 1) {
893  txt.insert(pos + 1, "<<");
894  if (txt.back() != '.')
895  txt += '.';
896  txt += ">>.";
897  }
898  }
899  else if (txt.back() != '.')
900  txt += '.';
901  txt += "_self";
902  auto path = App::ObjectIdentifier::parse(objs.front(), txt);
903  if (path.getPropertyName() != "_self") {
904  FC_TRACE("Object " << txt << " not found in " << doc->getName());
905  return;
906  }
907  auto obj = path.getDocumentObject();
908  if (!obj) {
909  FC_TRACE("Object " << txt << " not found in " << doc->getName());
910  return;
911  }
912  std::string subname = path.getSubObjectName();
913  App::DocumentObject* parent = nullptr;
914  if (searchContextDoc) {
915  auto it = DocumentMap.find(searchContextDoc);
916  if (it != DocumentMap.end()) {
917  parent = it->second->getTopParent(obj, subname);
918  if (parent) {
919  obj = parent;
920  docItem = it->second;
921  doc = docItem->document()->getDocument();
922  }
923  }
924  }
925  if (!parent) {
926  parent = docItem->getTopParent(obj, subname);
927  while (!parent) {
928  if (docItem->document()->getDocument() == obj->getDocument()) {
929  // this shouldn't happen
930  FC_LOG("Object " << txt << " not found in " << doc->getName());
931  return;
932  }
933  auto it = DocumentMap.find(Application::Instance->getDocument(obj->getDocument()));
934  if (it == DocumentMap.end())
935  return;
936  docItem = it->second;
937  parent = docItem->getTopParent(obj, subname);
938  }
939  obj = parent;
940  }
941  auto item = docItem->findItemByObject(true, obj, subname.c_str());
942  if (!item) {
943  FC_TRACE("item " << txt << " not found in " << doc->getName());
944  return;
945  }
946  scrollToItem(item);
947  Selection().setPreselect(obj->getDocument()->getName(),
948  obj->getNameInDocument(), subname.c_str(), 0, 0, 0,
949  SelectionChanges::MsgSource::TreeView);
950  if (select) {
951  Gui::Selection().selStackPush();
952  Gui::Selection().clearSelection();
953  Gui::Selection().addSelection(obj->getDocument()->getName(),
954  obj->getNameInDocument(), subname.c_str());
955  Gui::Selection().selStackPush();
956  }
957  else {
958  searchObject = item->object()->getObject();
959  item->setBackground(0, QColor(255, 255, 0, 100));
960  }
961  FC_TRACE("found item " << txt);
962  }
963  catch (...)
964  {
965  FC_TRACE("item " << txt << " search exception in " << doc->getName());
966  }
967 }

985 void TreeWidget::_updateStatus(bool delay) {
986  // When running from a different thread Qt will raise a warning
987  // when trying to start the QTimer
988  if (Q_UNLIKELY(thread() != QThread::currentThread())) {
989  return;
990  }
991 
992  if (!delay) {
993  if (!ChangedObjects.empty() || !NewObjects.empty())
994  onUpdateStatus();
995  return;
996  }
997  int timeout = TreeParams::getStatusTimeout();
998  if (timeout < 0)
999  timeout = 1;
1000  statusTimer->start(timeout);
1001 }

1003 void TreeWidget::contextMenuEvent(QContextMenuEvent* e)
1004 {
1005  // ask workbenches and view provider, ...
1006  MenuItem view;
1007  Gui::Application::Instance->setupContextMenu("Tree", &view);
1008 
1009  view << "Std_Properties" << "Separator" << "Std_Expressions";
1010  Workbench::createLinkMenu(&view);
1011 
1012  QMenu contextMenu;
1013 
1014  QMenu subMenu;
1015  QMenu editMenu;
1016  QActionGroup subMenuGroup(&subMenu);
1017  subMenuGroup.setExclusive(true);
1018  connect(&subMenuGroup, &QActionGroup::triggered,
1019  this, &TreeWidget::onActivateDocument);
1020  MenuManager::getInstance()->setupContextMenu(&view, contextMenu);
1021 
1022  // get the current item
1023  this->contextItem = itemAt(e->pos());
1024 
1025  if (this->contextItem && this->contextItem->type() == DocumentType) {
1026  auto docitem = static_cast<DocumentItem*>(this->contextItem);
1027  App::Document* doc = docitem->document()->getDocument();
1028 
1029  // It's better to let user decide whether and how to activate
1030  // the current document, such as by double-clicking.
1031  // App::GetApplication().setActiveDocument(doc);
1032 
1033  showHiddenAction->setChecked(docitem->showHidden());
1034  contextMenu.addAction(this->showHiddenAction);
1035  contextMenu.addAction(this->searchObjectsAction);
1036  contextMenu.addAction(this->closeDocAction);
1037  if (doc->testStatus(App::Document::PartialDoc))
1038  contextMenu.addAction(this->reloadDocAction);
1039  else {
1040  for (auto d : doc->getDependentDocuments()) {
1041  if (d->testStatus(App::Document::PartialDoc)) {
1042  contextMenu.addAction(this->reloadDocAction);
1043  break;
1044  }
1045  }
1046  contextMenu.addAction(this->selectDependentsAction);
1047  this->skipRecomputeAction->setChecked(doc->testStatus(App::Document::SkipRecompute));
1048  contextMenu.addAction(this->skipRecomputeAction);
1049  this->allowPartialRecomputeAction->setChecked(doc->testStatus(App::Document::AllowPartialRecompute));
1050  if (doc->testStatus(App::Document::SkipRecompute))
1051  contextMenu.addAction(this->allowPartialRecomputeAction);
1052  contextMenu.addAction(this->markRecomputeAction);
1053  contextMenu.addAction(this->createGroupAction);
1054  }
1055  contextMenu.addSeparator();
1056  }
1057  else if (this->contextItem && this->contextItem->type() == ObjectType) {
1058  auto objitem = static_cast<DocumentObjectItem*>
1059  (this->contextItem);
1060 
1061  // check that the selection is not across several documents
1062  bool acrossDocuments = false;
1063  auto SelectedObjectsList = Selection().getCompleteSelection();
1064  // get the object's document as reference
1065  App::Document* doc = objitem->object()->getObject()->getDocument();
1066  for (auto it = SelectedObjectsList.begin(); it != SelectedObjectsList.end(); ++it) {
1067  if ((*it).pDoc != doc) {
1068  acrossDocuments = true;
1069  break;
1070  }
1071  }
1072 
1073  showHiddenAction->setChecked(doc->ShowHidden.getValue());
1074  contextMenu.addAction(this->showHiddenAction);
1075  contextMenu.addAction(this->toggleVisibilityInTreeAction);
1076 
1077  if (!acrossDocuments) { // is only sensible for selections within one document
1078  if (objitem->object()->getObject()->isDerivedFrom(App::DocumentObjectGroup::getClassTypeId()))
1079  contextMenu.addAction(this->createGroupAction);
1080  // if there are dependent objects in the selection, add context menu to add them to selection
1081  if (CheckForDependents())
1082  contextMenu.addAction(this->selectDependentsAction);
1083  }
1084 
1085  contextMenu.addSeparator();
1086  contextMenu.addAction(this->markRecomputeAction);
1087  contextMenu.addAction(this->recomputeObjectAction);
1088  contextMenu.addSeparator();
1089 
1090  // relabeling is only possible for a single selected document
1091  if (SelectedObjectsList.size() == 1)
1092  contextMenu.addAction(this->relabelObjectAction);
1093 
1094  auto selItems = this->selectedItems();
1095  // if only one item is selected, setup the edit menu
1096  if (selItems.size() == 1) {
1097  objitem->object()->setupContextMenu(&editMenu, this, SLOT(onStartEditing()));
1098  QList<QAction*> editAct = editMenu.actions();
1099  if (!editAct.isEmpty()) {
1100  QAction* topact = contextMenu.actions().constFirst();
1101  for (QList<QAction*>::iterator it = editAct.begin(); it != editAct.end(); ++it)
1102  contextMenu.insertAction(topact, *it);
1103  QAction* first = editAct.front();
1104  contextMenu.setDefaultAction(first);
1105  if (objitem->object()->isEditing())
1106  contextMenu.insertAction(topact, this->finishEditingAction);
1107  contextMenu.insertSeparator(topact);
1108  }
1109  }
1110  }
1111 
1112 
1113  // add a submenu to active a document if two or more exist
1114  std::vector<App::Document*> docs = App::GetApplication().getDocuments();
1115  if (docs.size() >= 2) {
1116  contextMenu.addSeparator();
1117  App::Document* activeDoc = App::GetApplication().getActiveDocument();
1118  subMenu.setTitle(tr("Activate document"));
1119  contextMenu.addMenu(&subMenu);
1120  QAction* active = nullptr;
1121  for (auto it = docs.begin(); it != docs.end(); ++it) {
1122  QString label = QString::fromUtf8((*it)->Label.getValue());
1123  QAction* action = subMenuGroup.addAction(label);
1124  action->setCheckable(true);
1125  action->setStatusTip(tr("Activate document %1").arg(label));
1126  action->setData(QByteArray((*it)->getName()));
1127  if (*it == activeDoc) active = action;
1128  }
1129 
1130  if (active)
1131  active->setChecked(true);
1132  subMenu.addActions(subMenuGroup.actions());
1133  }
1134 
1135  // add a submenu to present the settings of the tree.
1136  QMenu settingsMenu;
1137  settingsMenu.setTitle(tr("Tree settings"));
1138  contextMenu.addSeparator();
1139  contextMenu.addMenu(&settingsMenu);
1140 
1141  QAction* action = new QAction(tr("Show description"), this);
1142  QAction* internalNameAction = new QAction(tr("Show internal name"), this);
1143  action->setStatusTip(tr("Show a description column for items. An item's description can be set by pressing F2 (or your OS's edit button) or by editing the 'label2' property."));
1144  action->setCheckable(true);
1145 
1146  ParameterGrp::handle hGrp = App::GetApplication().GetParameterGroupByPath("User parameter:BaseApp/Preferences/TreeView");
1147  action->setChecked(!hGrp->GetBool("HideColumn", true));
1148

1159  internalNameAction->setCheckable(true);
1160 
1161  internalNameAction->setChecked(!hGrp->GetBool("HideInternalNames", true));
1162

1166  bool show = internalNameAction->isChecked();
1167  hGrp->SetBool("HideInternalNames", !show);
1168  setColumnHidden(2, !show);

1171 
1172  if (contextMenu.actions().count() > 0) {

1174  contextMenu.exec(QCursor::pos());

1268 // check if selection has dependent objects
1269 bool TreeWidget::CheckForDependents()
1270 {
1271  // if the selected object is a document
1272  if (this->contextItem && this->contextItem->type() == DocumentType) {
1273  return true;
1274  }
1275  // it can be an object
1276  else {
1277  QList<QTreeWidgetItem*> items = this->selectedItems();
1278  for (QList<QTreeWidgetItem*>::iterator it = items.begin(); it != items.end(); ++it) {
1279  if ((*it)->type() == ObjectType) {
1280  auto objitem = static_cast<DocumentObjectItem*>(*it);
1281  App::DocumentObject* obj = objitem->object()->getObject();
1282  // get dependents
1283  auto subObjectList = obj->getOutList();
1284  if (!subObjectList.empty())
1285  return true;
1286  }
1287  }
1288  }
1289 
1290  return false;
1291 }

1293 // adds an App::DocumentObject* and its dependent objects to the selection
1294 void TreeWidget::addDependentToSelection(App::Document* doc, App::DocumentObject* docObject)
1295 {
1296  // add the docObject to the selection
1297  Selection().addSelection(doc->getName(), docObject->getNameInDocument());
1298  // get the dependent
1299  auto subObjectList = docObject->getOutList();
1300  // the dependent can in turn have dependents, thus add them recursively
1301  for (auto itDepend = subObjectList.begin(); itDepend != subObjectList.end(); ++itDepend)
1302  addDependentToSelection(doc, (*itDepend));
1303 }

1305 // add dependents of the selected tree object to selection
1306 void TreeWidget::onSelectDependents()
1307 {
1308  // We only have this context menu entry if the selection is within one document but it
1309  // might be not the active document. Therefore get the document not here but later by casting.
1310  App::Document* doc;
1311 
1312  // if the selected object is a document
1313  if (this->contextItem && this->contextItem->type() == DocumentType) {
1314  auto docitem = static_cast<DocumentItem*>(this->contextItem);
1315  doc = docitem->document()->getDocument();
1316  std::vector<App::DocumentObject*> obj = doc->getObjects();
1317  for (auto it = obj.begin(); it != obj.end(); ++it)
1318  Selection().addSelection(doc->getName(), (*it)->getNameInDocument());
1319  }
1320  // it can be an object
1321  else {
1322  QList<QTreeWidgetItem*> items = this->selectedItems();
1323  for (QList<QTreeWidgetItem*>::iterator it = items.begin(); it != items.end(); ++it) {
1324  if ((*it)->type() == ObjectType) {
1325  auto objitem = static_cast<DocumentObjectItem*>(*it);
1326  doc = objitem->object()->getObject()->getDocument();
1327  App::DocumentObject* obj = objitem->object()->getObject();
1328  // the dependents can also have dependents, thus add them recursively via a separate void
1329  addDependentToSelection(doc, obj);
1330  }
1331  }
1332  }
1333 }

1497 std::vector<TreeWidget::SelInfo> TreeWidget::getSelection(App::Document* doc)
1498 {
1499  std::vector<SelInfo> ret;
1500 
1501  TreeWidget* tree = instance();
1502  if (!tree || !tree->isSelectionAttached()) {
1503  for (auto pTree : Instances)
1504  if (pTree->isSelectionAttached()) {
1505  tree = pTree;
1506  break;
1507  }
1508  }
1509  if (!tree)
1510  return ret;
1511 
1512  if (tree->selectTimer->isActive())
1513  tree->onSelectTimer();
1514  else
1515  tree->_updateStatus(false);
1516 
1517  const auto items = tree->selectedItems();
1518  for (auto ti : items) {
1519  if (ti->type() != ObjectType)
1520  continue;
1521  auto item = static_cast<DocumentObjectItem*>(ti);
1522  auto vp = item->object();
1523  auto obj = vp->getObject();
1524  if (!obj || !obj->isAttachedToDocument()) {
1525  FC_WARN("skip invalid object");
1526  continue;
1527  }
1528  if (doc && obj->getDocument() != doc) {
1529  FC_LOG("skip objects not from current document");
1530  continue;
1531  }
1532  ViewProviderDocumentObject* parentVp = nullptr;
1533  auto parent = item->getParentItem();
1534  if (parent) {
1535  parentVp = parent->object();
1536  if (!parentVp->getObject()->isAttachedToDocument()) {
1537  FC_WARN("skip '" << obj->getFullName() << "' with invalid parent");
1538  continue;
1539  }
1540  }
1541  ret.emplace_back();
1542  auto& sel = ret.back();
1543  sel.topParent = nullptr;
1544  std::ostringstream ss;
1545  item->getSubName(ss, sel.topParent);
1546  if (!sel.topParent)
1547  sel.topParent = obj;
1548  else
1549  ss << obj->getNameInDocument() << '.';
1550  sel.subname = ss.str();
1551  sel.parentVp = parentVp;
1552  sel.vp = vp;
1553  }
1554  return ret;
1555 }

1612 bool TreeWidget::eventFilter(QObject*, QEvent* ev) {
1613  switch (ev->type()) {
1614  case QEvent::KeyPress:
1615  case QEvent::KeyRelease: {
1616  auto ke = static_cast<QKeyEvent*>(ev);
1617  if (ke->key() != Qt::Key_Escape) {
1618  // Qt 5 only recheck key modifier on mouse move, so generate a fake
1619  // event to trigger drag cursor change
1620  auto mouseEvent = new QMouseEvent(QEvent::MouseMove,
1621  mapFromGlobal(QCursor::pos()), QCursor::pos(), Qt::NoButton,
1622  QApplication::mouseButtons(), QApplication::queryKeyboardModifiers());
1623  QApplication::postEvent(this, mouseEvent);
1624  }
1625  break;
1626  }
1627  default:
1628  break;
1629  }
1630  return false;
1631 }

1642 void TreeWidget::keyPressEvent(QKeyEvent* event)
1643 {
1644  if (event->matches(QKeySequence::Find)) {
1645  event->accept();
1646  onSearchObjects();
1647  return;
1648  }
1649  else if (event->modifiers() == Qt::AltModifier) {
1650  if (event->key() == Qt::Key_Left) {
1651  for (auto& item : selectedItems()) {
1652  item->setExpanded(false);
1653  }
1654  event->accept();
1655  return;
1656  }
1657  else if (event->key() == Qt::Key_Right) {
1658  for (auto& item : selectedItems()) {
1659  item->setExpanded(true);
1660  }
1661  event->accept();
1662  return;
1663  }
1664  else if (event->key() == Qt::Key_Up) {
1665  for (auto& item : selectedItems()) {
1666  item->setExpanded(true);
1667  for (auto& child : childrenOfItem(*item)) {
1668  child->setExpanded(false);
1669  }
1670  }
1671  event->accept();
1672  return;
1673  }
1674  else if (event->key() == Qt::Key_Down) {
1675  for (auto& item : selectedItems()) {
1676  item->setExpanded(true);
1677  for (auto& child : childrenOfItem(*item)) {
1678  child->setExpanded(true);
1679  }
1680  }
1681  event->accept();
1682  return;
1683  }
1684  }
1685  else if (event->key() == Qt::Key_Left) {
1686  auto index = currentIndex();
1687  if (index.column() == 1) {
1688  setCurrentIndex(model()->index(index.row(), 0, index.parent()));
1689  event->accept();
1690  return;
1691  }
1692  }
1693  else if (event->key() == Qt::Key_Right) {
1694  auto index = currentIndex();
1695  if (index.column() == 0) {
1696  setCurrentIndex(model()->index(index.row(), 1, index.parent()));
1697  event->accept();
1698  return;
1699  }
1700  }
1701  QTreeWidget::keyPressEvent(event);
1702 }

1704 void TreeWidget::mousePressEvent(QMouseEvent* event)
1705 {
1706  if (isVisibilityIconEnabled()) {
1707  QTreeWidgetItem* item = itemAt(event->pos());
1708  if (item && item->type() == TreeWidget::ObjectType && event->button() == Qt::LeftButton) {
1709  auto objitem = static_cast<DocumentObjectItem*>(item);
1710 
1711  // Mouse position relative to viewport
1712  auto mousePos = event->pos();
1713 
1714  // Rect occupied by the item relative to viewport
1715  auto iconRect = visualItemRect(objitem);
1716 
1717  auto style = this->style();
1718 
1719  // If the checkboxes are visible, these are displayed before the icon
1720  // and we have to compensate for its width.
1721  if (isSelectionCheckBoxesEnabled()) {
1722  int checkboxWidth = style->pixelMetric(QStyle::PM_IndicatorWidth)
1723  + style->pixelMetric(QStyle::PM_LayoutHorizontalSpacing);
1724  iconRect.adjust(checkboxWidth, 0, 0, 0);
1725  }
1726 
1727  int const margin = style->pixelMetric(QStyle::PM_FocusFrameHMargin) + 1;
1728  iconRect.adjust(margin, 0, 0, 0);
1729 
1730  // We are interested in the first icon (visibility icon)
1731  iconRect.setWidth(iconSize());
1732 
1733  // If the visibility icon was clicked, toggle the DocumentObject visibility
1734  if (iconRect.contains(mousePos)) {
1735  auto obj = objitem->object()->getObject();
1736  char const* objname = obj->getNameInDocument();
1737 
1738  App::DocumentObject* parent = nullptr;
1739  std::ostringstream subName;
1740  objitem->getSubName(subName, parent);
1741 
1742  // Try the ElementVisible API, if that is not supported toggle the Visibility property
1743  int visible = -1;
1744  if (parent) {
1745  visible = parent->isElementVisible(objname);
1746  }
1747  if (parent && visible >= 0) {
1748  parent->setElementVisible(objname, !visible);
1749  } else {
1750  visible = obj->Visibility.getValue();
1751  obj->Visibility.setValue(!visible);
1752  }
1753  }
1754  }
1755  }

1757  QTreeWidget::mousePressEvent(event);
1758 }

1760 void TreeWidget::mouseDoubleClickEvent(QMouseEvent* event)
1761 {
1762  QTreeWidgetItem* item = itemAt(event->pos());
1763  if (!item)
1764  return;
1765 
1766  try {
1767  if (item->type() == TreeWidget::DocumentType) {
1768  Gui::Document* doc = static_cast<DocumentItem*>(item)->document();
1769  if (!doc)
1770  return;
1771  if (doc->getDocument()->testStatus(App::Document::PartialDoc)) {
1772  contextItem = item;
1773  onReloadDoc();
1774  return;
1775  }
1776  if (!doc->setActiveView())
1777  doc->setActiveView(nullptr, View3DInventor::getClassTypeId());
1778  }
1779  else if (item->type() == TreeWidget::ObjectType) {
1780  auto objitem = static_cast<DocumentObjectItem*>(item);
1781  ViewProviderDocumentObject* vp = objitem->object();
1782 
1783  objitem->getOwnerDocument()->document()->setActiveView(vp);
1784  auto manager = Application::Instance->macroManager();
1785  auto lines = manager->getLines();
1786 
1787  std::ostringstream ss;
1788  ss << Command::getObjectCmd(vp->getObject())
1789  << ".ViewObject.doubleClicked()";
1790 
1791  const char* commandText = vp->getTransactionText();
1792  if (commandText) {
1793  auto editDoc = Application::Instance->editDocument();
1794  App::AutoTransaction committer(commandText, true);
1795 
1796  if (!vp->doubleClicked())
1797  QTreeWidget::mouseDoubleClickEvent(event);
1798  else if (lines == manager->getLines())
1799  manager->addLine(MacroManager::Gui, ss.str().c_str());
1800 
1801  // If the double click starts an editing, let the transaction persist
1802  if (!editDoc && Application::Instance->editDocument())
1803  committer.setEnable(false);
1804  }
1805  else {
1806  if (!vp->doubleClicked())
1807  QTreeWidget::mouseDoubleClickEvent(event);
1808  else if (lines == manager->getLines())
1809  manager->addLine(MacroManager::Gui, ss.str().c_str());
1810  }
1811  }
1812  }
1813  catch (Base::Exception& e) {
1814  e.ReportException();
1815  }
1816  catch (std::exception& e) {
1817  FC_ERR("C++ exception: " << e.what());
1818  }
1819  catch (...) {
1820  FC_ERR("Unknown exception");
1821  }
1822 }

1893  {

1908  const auto& subnames = item->getSubNames();
1909  info.second.insert(info.second.end(), subnames.begin(), subnames.end());
1910  }

1977 void TreeWidget::dragMoveEvent(QDragMoveEvent* event)
1978 {
1979  // Qt5 does not change drag cursor in response to modifier key press,
1980  // because QDrag installs a event filter that eats up key event. We install
1981  // a filter after Qt and generate fake mouse move event in response to key
1982  // press event, which triggers QDrag to update its cursor
1983  if (!_DragEventFilter) {
1984  _DragEventFilter = true;
1985  qApp->installEventFilter(this);
1986  }
1987 
1988  QTreeWidget::dragMoveEvent(event);
1989  if (!event->isAccepted()) {
1990  //return;
1991  // QTreeWidget::dragMoveEvent is rejecting the event when in between items
1992  // at DocumentItem root level. Which is preventing reordering. To work around
1993  // we accept for now, then reject below if targetItem not found.
1994  event->accept();

1999  QTreeWidgetItem* targetItem = targetInfo.targetItem;
2000  if (!targetItem) {
2001  event->ignore();

2003  }
2004

2006 
2007  auto da = getDropAction(items.size(), targetItem->type());

2009 
2010  if (targetItem->type() == TreeWidget::DocumentType) {
2011  leaveEvent(nullptr);
2012  }
2013  else if (targetItem->type() == TreeWidget::ObjectType) {
2014  onItemEntered(targetItem);
2015

2017  Gui::ViewProviderDocumentObject* vp = targetItemObj->object();
2018

2020  if (da == Qt::MoveAction && (targetInfo.inThresholdZone || !vp->canDropObjects())) {
2021  targetInfo.targetItem = targetInfo.targetItem->parent();

2023  leaveEvent(nullptr);
2024  return;
2025  }
2026

2028  vp = targetItemObj->object();
2029 
2030  if (!vp) {
2031  TREE_TRACE("cannot drop");
2032  return;
2033  }
2034  }
2035  try {
2036  if (da != Qt::LinkAction && !vp->canDropObjects()) {
2037  if (!(event->possibleActions() & Qt::LinkAction) || items.size() != 1) {
2038  TREE_TRACE("Cannot drop here");
2039  event->ignore();
2040  return;
2041  }
2042  }

2044  if (ti->type() != TreeWidget::ObjectType) {
2045  TREE_TRACE("cannot drop");

2047  return;
2048  }

2050

2052

2057  {
2058  TREE_TRACE("Cannot drag object");
2059  event->ignore();
2060  return;
2061  }
2062  }
2063

2065  auto owner = item->getRelativeParent(str, targetItemObj);
2066  auto subname = str.str();

2069  if (da != Qt::LinkAction && !vp->canDropObjectEx(obj, owner, subname.c_str(), item->mySubs)) {
2070  TREE_TRACE("cannot drop " << obj->getFullName() << ' ' << (owner ? owner->getFullName() : "<No Owner>") << '.' << subname);
2071  event->ignore();
2072  return;
2073  }
2074  }
2075  }
2076  catch (Base::Exception& e) {
2077  e.ReportException();
2078  event->ignore();
2079  }
2080  catch (std::exception& e) {
2081  FC_ERR("C++ exception: " << e.what());
2082  event->ignore();
2083  }
2084  catch (...) {
2085  FC_ERR("Unknown exception");
2086  event->ignore();
2087  }
2088  }
2089  else {
2090  leaveEvent(nullptr);
2091  event->ignore();
2092  }
2093 }

2095 TreeWidget::TargetItemInfo TreeWidget::getTargetInfo(QEvent* ev)
2096 {
2097  TargetItemInfo targetInfo;
2098 
2099  QPoint pos = getPos(ev);
2100  if (pos == QPoint(-1, -1)) {
2101  return {}; // Return an empty struct
2102  }
2103 
2104  targetInfo.targetItem = itemAt(pos);
2105  // not dropped onto an item or one of the source items is also the destination item
2106  if (!targetInfo.targetItem || targetInfo.targetItem->isSelected()) {
2107  return {};
2108  }
2109  targetInfo.underMouseItem = targetInfo.targetItem;
2110 
2111  if (targetInfo.targetItem->type() == TreeWidget::ObjectType) {
2112  auto targetItemObj = static_cast<DocumentObjectItem*>(targetInfo.targetItem);
2113  targetInfo.targetDoc = targetItemObj->getOwnerDocument()->document()->getDocument();
2114  }
2115  else if (targetInfo.targetItem->type() == TreeWidget::DocumentType) {
2116  auto targetDocItem = static_cast<DocumentItem*>(targetInfo.targetItem);
2117  targetInfo.targetDoc = targetDocItem->document()->getDocument();
2118  }
2119  else {
2120  return {};
2121  }
2122 
2123  // Calculate the position of the mouse relative to the item's rectangle
2124  QRect itemRect = visualItemRect(targetInfo.targetItem);
2125  int mouseY = pos.y();
2126  int itemMidPoint = itemRect.top() + itemRect.height() / 2;
2127  int threshold = itemRect.height() * 0.20; // 20% of the item's height as threshold
2128 
2129  targetInfo.inBottomHalf = mouseY > itemMidPoint;
2130  targetInfo.inThresholdZone = ((mouseY < itemRect.top() + threshold) && !targetInfo.targetItem->isExpanded())
2131  || (mouseY > itemRect.top() + itemRect.height() - threshold);
2132  return targetInfo;
2133 }

2607  continue;
2608  }
2609 
2610  Gui::Command::runCommand(Gui::Command::App, ss.str().c_str());
2611 
2612  }
2613  else {
2614  ss << Command::getObjectCmd(vp->getObject())
2615  << ".ViewObject.dropObject(" << Command::getObjectCmd(obj);
2616  if (owner) {
2617  ss << "," << Command::getObjectCmd(owner)
2618  << ",'" << subname << "',[";
2619  }
2620  else
2621  ss << ",None,'',[";
2622  for (auto& sub : info.subs)
2623  ss << "'" << sub << "',";
2624  ss << "])";
2625  auto lines = manager->getLines();
2626  dropName = vp->dropObjectEx(obj, owner, subname.c_str(), info.subs);
2627  if (manager->getLines() == lines)
2628  manager->addLine(MacroManager::Gui, ss.str().c_str());
2629  if (!dropName.empty())
2630  dropName = targetSubname.str() + dropName;
2631  }
2632 
2633  touched = true;
2634 
2635  // Construct the subname pointing to the dropped object
2636  if (dropName.empty()) {
2637  auto pos = targetSubname.tellp();
2638  targetSubname << obj->getNameInDocument() << '.' << std::ends;
2639  dropName = targetSubname.str();
2640  targetSubname.seekp(pos);
2641  }
2642 
2643  Base::Matrix4D newMat;
2644  auto sobj = dropParent->getSubObject(dropName.c_str(), nullptr, &newMat);
2645  if (!sobj) {
2646  FC_LOG("failed to find dropped object "
2647  << dropParent->getFullName() << '.' << dropName);
2648  setSelection = false;
2649  continue;
2650  }
2651 
2652  if (da != Qt::CopyAction && propPlacement) {
2653  // try to adjust placement
2654  if ((info.dragging && sobj == obj) ||
2655  (!info.dragging && sobj->getLinkedObject(false) == obj))
2656  {
2657  if (!info.dragging)
2658  propPlacement = Base::freecad_dynamic_cast<App::PropertyPlacement>(
2659  sobj->getPropertyByName("Placement"));
2660  if (propPlacement) {
2661  newMat *= propPlacement->getValue().inverse().toMatrix();
2662  newMat.inverseGauss();
2663  Base::Placement pla(newMat * mat);
2664  propPlacement->setValueIfChanged(pla);
2665  }
2666  }
2667  }
2668  droppedObjects.emplace_back(dropParent, dropName);
2669  draggedObjects.push_back(obj);
2670  }
2671  Base::FlagToggler<> guard(_DisableCheckTopParent);
2672  if (setSelection && !droppedObjects.empty()) {
2673  Selection().selStackPush();
2674  Selection().clearCompleteSelection();
2675  for (auto& v : droppedObjects) {
2676  Selection().addSelection(v.first->getDocument()->getName(),
2677  v.first->getNameInDocument(), v.second.c_str());
2678  }
2679  Selection().selStackPush();
2680  }
2681 
2682  // If moved, then we sort objects properly.
2683  if (da == Qt::MoveAction && vp->acceptReorderingObjects()) {
2684  sortDroppedObjects(targetInfo, draggedObjects);
2685  }
2686  }
2687  catch (const Base::Exception& e) {
2688  e.ReportException();
2689  errMsg = e.what();
2690  }
2691  catch (std::exception& e) {
2692  FC_ERR("C++ exception: " << e.what());
2693  errMsg = e.what();
2694  }
2695  catch (...) {
2696  FC_ERR("Unknown exception");
2697  errMsg = "Unknown exception";
2698  }
2699  if (!errMsg.empty()) {
2700  committer.close(true);
2701  QMessageBox::critical(getMainWindow(), QObject::tr("Drag & drop failed"),
2702  QString::fromUtf8(errMsg.c_str()));
2703  return false;
2704  }
2705  return touched;
2706 }

2759 void TreeWidget::sortDroppedObjects(TargetItemInfo& targetInfo, std::vector<App::DocumentObject*> draggedObjects)
2760 {
2761  if (targetInfo.targetItem == targetInfo.underMouseItem) {
2762  return;
2763  }
2764  auto underMouseItemObj = static_cast<DocumentObjectItem*>(targetInfo.underMouseItem);
2765  auto underMouseObj = underMouseItemObj->object()->getObject();
2766  std::vector<App::DocumentObject*> sortedObjList;
2767  std::vector<App::DocumentObject*> objList;
2768 
2769  auto sortIntoList = [&sortedObjList, &draggedObjects, underMouseObj, &targetInfo](const std::vector<App::DocumentObject*>& objects) {
2770  for (auto* obj : objects) {
2771  if (obj == underMouseObj) {
2772  if (targetInfo.inBottomHalf) {
2773  sortedObjList.push_back(obj);
2774  }
2775 
2776  for (auto* draggedObj : draggedObjects) {
2777  sortedObjList.push_back(draggedObj);
2778  }
2779 
2780  if (!targetInfo.inBottomHalf) {
2781  sortedObjList.push_back(obj);
2782  }
2783  }
2784  else {
2785  if (std::find(draggedObjects.begin(), draggedObjects.end(), obj) == draggedObjects.end()) {
2786  sortedObjList.push_back(obj);
2787  }
2788  }
2789  }
2790  };
2791 
2792  if (targetInfo.targetItem->type() == TreeWidget::ObjectType) {
2793  // To update the order of items of groups such as App::Part, we just need to change the order in the Group property
2794  auto targetItemObj = static_cast<DocumentObjectItem*>(targetInfo.targetItem);
2795  App::DocumentObject* targetObj = targetItemObj->object()->getObject();
2796 
2797  auto propGroup = Base::freecad_dynamic_cast<App::PropertyLinkList>(targetObj->getPropertyByName("Group"));
2798  if (!propGroup) {
2799  return;
2800  }
2801 
2802  objList = propGroup->getValue();
2803  sortIntoList(objList); // Move dropped objects to correct position
2804  propGroup->setValue(sortedObjList);
2805  }
2806  else if (targetInfo.targetItem->type() == TreeWidget::DocumentType) {
2807  Gui::Document* guiDoc = Gui::Application::Instance->getDocument(targetInfo.targetDoc->getName());
2808  objList = guiDoc->getTreeRootObjects();
2809  // First we need to sort objList by treeRank.
2810  std::sort(objList.begin(), objList.end(),
2811  [](App::DocumentObject* a, App::DocumentObject* b) {
2812  auto vpA = dynamic_cast<Gui::ViewProviderDocumentObject*>(Gui::Application::Instance->getViewProvider(a));
2813  auto vpB = dynamic_cast<Gui::ViewProviderDocumentObject*>(Gui::Application::Instance->getViewProvider(b));
2814  if (vpA && vpB) {
2815  return vpA->getTreeRank() < vpB->getTreeRank();
2816  }
2817  return false; // Keep the original order if either vpA or vpB is nullptr
2818  });
2819 
2820  // Then we move dropped objects to their correct position
2821  sortIntoList(objList);
2822 
2823  // Then we set the tree rank
2824  for (size_t i = 0; i < sortedObjList.size(); ++i) {
2825  auto vp = dynamic_cast<ViewProviderDocumentObject*>(Application::Instance->getViewProvider(sortedObjList[i]));
2826  vp->setTreeRank(i);
2827  }
2828 
2829  // Lastly we refresh the tree
2830  static_cast<DocumentItem*>(targetInfo.targetItem)->sortObjectItems();
2831  }
2832 }

2949 struct UpdateDisabler {
2950  QWidget& widget;
2951  int& blocked;
2952  bool visible{false};
2953  bool focus{false};
2954 
2955  // Note! DO NOT block signal here, or else
2956  // QTreeWidgetItem::setChildIndicatorPolicy() does not work
2957  UpdateDisabler(QWidget& w, int& blocked)
2958  : widget(w), blocked(blocked)
2959  {
2960  if (++blocked > 1)
2961  return;
2962  focus = widget.hasFocus();
2963  visible = widget.isVisible();
2964  if (visible) {
2965  // setUpdatesEnabled(false) does not seem to speed up anything.
2966  // setVisible(false) on the other hand makes QTreeWidget::setData
2967  // (i.e. any change to QTreeWidgetItem) faster by 10+ times.
2968  //
2969  // widget.setUpdatesEnabled(false);
2970 
2971  widget.setVisible(false);
2972  }
2973  }
2974  ~UpdateDisabler() {
2975  if (blocked <= 0 || --blocked != 0)
2976  return;
2977 
2978  if (visible) {
2979  widget.setVisible(true);
2980  if (focus)
2981  widget.setFocus();
2982  }
2983  }
2984 };

2986 void TreeWidget::onUpdateStatus()
2987 {

2989  _updateStatus();
2990  return;
2991  }
2992 
2993  for (auto& v : DocumentMap) {
2994  if (v.first->isPerformingTransaction()) {
2995  // We have to delay item creation until undo/redo is done, because the
2996  // object re-creation while in transaction may break tree view item
2997  // update logic. For example, a parent object re-created before its
2998  // children, but the parent's link property already contains all the
2999  // (detached) children.
3000  _updateStatus();
3001  return;
3002  }
3003  }
3004 
3005  FC_LOG("begin update status");
3006 
3007  UpdateDisabler disabler(*this, updateBlocked);
3008

3010 
3011  // Use a local copy in case of nested calls
3012  auto localNewObjects = NewObjects;
3013  NewObjects.clear();
3014 
3015  // Checking for new objects
3016  for (auto& v : localNewObjects) {
3017  auto doc = App::GetApplication().getDocument(v.first.c_str());
3018  if (!doc)
3019  continue;
3020  auto gdoc = Application::Instance->getDocument(doc);
3021  if (!gdoc)

3024  if (!docItem)
3025  continue;

3027  auto obj = doc->getObjectByID(id);

3035  if (vpd)

3040  // Use a local copy in case of nested calls
3041  auto localChangedObjects = ChangedObjects;
3042  ChangedObjects.clear();
3043

3046  auto obj = v.first;
3047 
3048  auto iter = ObjectTable.find(obj);
3049  if (iter == ObjectTable.end())
3050  continue;
3051

3054 
3055  if (!iter->second.empty()) {

3057  bool itemHidden = !data->viewObject->showInTree();

3067  }

3070  }

3075  pos->second->testStatus();

3077  TimingPrint();

3100  else if (docItem->_ExpandInfo) {

3103  bool legacy = name[0] == '*';
3104  if (legacy)

3107  if (!obj)
3108  continue;
3109  auto iter = docItem->ObjectMap.find(obj);
3110  if (iter == docItem->ObjectMap.end())

3138  if (activeDocItem) {
3139  auto it = activeDocItem->ObjectMap.find(obj);
3140  if (it != activeDocItem->ObjectMap.end())
3141  data = it->second;
3142  }

3419 void TreeWidget::onItemSelectionChanged()
3420 {
3421  if (!this->isSelectionAttached()
3422  || this->isSelectionBlocked()
3423  || updateBlocked)
3424  return;
3425 
3426  _LastSelectedTreeWidget = this;

3428  // block tmp. the connection to avoid to notify us ourself
3429  bool lock = this->blockSelection(true);

3434  _updateStatus(false);

3436  auto selItems = selectedItems();
3437

3439  if (!selItems.empty()) {
3440  auto firstType = selItems.back()->type();

3442  auto item = *it;

3459  // Gui.Selection and Tree view selection because of newly added
3460  // DocumentObject::redirectSubName()
3461  Selection().clearCompleteSelection();

3463  if (!selItems.empty()) {

3466  else if (selItems.front()->type() == DocumentType) {

3481  currentDocItem = nullptr;
3482  }
3483  if (TreeParams::getRecordSelection())
3484  Gui::Selection().selStackPush();
3485  }

3875 bool DocumentItem::createNewItem(const Gui::ViewProviderDocumentObject& obj,
3876  QTreeWidgetItem* parent, int index, DocumentObjectDataPtr data)
3877 {
3878  if (!obj.getObject() ||
3879  !obj.getObject()->isAttachedToDocument() ||
3880  obj.getObject()->testStatus(App::PartialObject))
3881  return false;
3882 
3883  if (!data) {
3884  auto& pdata = ObjectMap[obj.getObject()];
3885  if (!pdata) {
3886  pdata = std::make_shared<DocumentObjectData>(
3887  this, const_cast<ViewProviderDocumentObject*>(&obj));
3888  auto& entry = getTree()->ObjectTable[obj.getObject()];
3889  if (!entry.empty())
3890  pdata->updateChildren(*entry.begin());
3891  else
3892  pdata->updateChildren(true);
3893  entry.insert(pdata);
3894  }
3895  else if (pdata->rootItem && !parent) {
3896  Base::Console().Warning("DocumentItem::slotNewObject: Cannot add view provider twice.\n");
3897  return false;
3898  }
3899  data = pdata;
3900  }
3901 
3902  auto item = new DocumentObjectItem(this, data);
3903  if (!parent || parent == this) {
3904  parent = this;
3905  data->rootItem = item;

4044 void DocumentItem::populateItem(DocumentObjectItem* item, bool refresh, bool delay)
4045 {
4046  (void)delay;
4047 
4048  if (item->populated && !refresh)
4049  return;
4050 
4051  // Lazy loading policy: We will create an item for each children object if
4052  // a) the item is expanded, or b) there is at least one free child, i.e.
4053  // child originally located at root.
4054 
4055  item->setChildIndicatorPolicy(item->myData->children.empty() ?
4056  QTreeWidgetItem::DontShowIndicator : QTreeWidgetItem::ShowIndicator);
4057 
4058  if (!item->populated && !item->isExpanded()) {
4059  bool doPopulate = false;
4060 
4061  bool external = item->object()->getDocument() != item->getOwnerDocument()->document();
4062  if (external)
4063  return;
4064  auto obj = item->object()->getObject();
4065  auto linked = obj->getLinkedObject(true);
4066  if (linked && linked->getDocument() != obj->getDocument())
4067  return;
4068  for (auto child : item->myData->children) {
4069  auto it = ObjectMap.find(child);
4070  if (it == ObjectMap.end() || it->second->items.empty()) {
4071  auto vp = getViewProvider(child);
4072  if (!vp) continue;
4073  doPopulate = true;
4074  break;
4075  }
4076  if (item->myData->removeChildrenFromRoot) {
4077  if (it->second->rootItem) {
4078  doPopulate = true;
4079  break;
4080  }
4081  }
4082  }
4083 
4084  if (!doPopulate)
4085  return;
4086  }
4087 
4088  item->populated = true;
4089  bool checkHidden = !showHidden();
4090  bool updated = false;
4091 
4092  int i = -1;
4093  // iterate through the claimed children, and try to synchronize them with the
4094  // children tree item with the same order of appearance.
4095  int childCount = item->childCount();
4096  for (auto child : item->myData->children) {
4097 
4098  ++i; // the current index of the claimed child
4099 
4100  bool found = false;
4101  for (int j = i; j < childCount; ++j) {
4102  QTreeWidgetItem* ci = item->child(j);
4103  if (ci->type() != TreeWidget::ObjectType)
4104  continue;
4105 
4106  auto childItem = static_cast<DocumentObjectItem*>(ci);
4107  if (childItem->object()->getObject() != child)
4108  continue;
4109 
4110  found = true;
4111  if (j != i) { // fix index if it is changed
4112  childItem->setHighlight(false);
4113  item->removeChild(ci);
4114  item->insertChild(i, ci);
4115  assert(ci->parent() == item);
4116  if (checkHidden)
4117  updateItemsVisibility(ci, false);
4118  }
4119 
4120  // Check if the item just changed its policy of whether to remove
4121  // children item from the root.
4122  if (item->myData->removeChildrenFromRoot) {
4123  if (childItem->myData->rootItem) {
4124  assert(childItem != childItem->myData->rootItem);
4125  bool lock = getTree()->blockSelection(true);
4126  delete childItem->myData->rootItem;
4127  getTree()->blockSelection(lock);
4128  }
4129  }
4130  else if (childItem->requiredAtRoot()) {
4131  createNewItem(*childItem->object(), this, -1, childItem->myData);
4132  updated = true;
4133  }
4134  break;
4135  }
4136 
4137  if (found)
4138  continue;
4139 
4140  // This algo will be recursively applied to newly created child items
4141  // through slotNewObject -> populateItem
4142 
4143  auto it = ObjectMap.find(child);
4144  if (it == ObjectMap.end() || it->second->items.empty()) {
4145  auto vp = getViewProvider(child);
4146  if (!vp || !createNewItem(*vp, item, i, it == ObjectMap.end() ? DocumentObjectDataPtr() : it->second))
4147  --i;
4148  else
4149  updated = true;
4150  continue;
4151  }
4152 
4153  if (!item->myData->removeChildrenFromRoot || !it->second->rootItem) {
4154  DocumentObjectItem* childItem = *it->second->items.begin();
4155  if (!createNewItem(*childItem->object(), item, i, it->second))
4156  --i;
4157  else
4158  updated = true;
4159  }
4160  else {
4161  DocumentObjectItem* childItem = it->second->rootItem;
4162  if (item == childItem || item->isChildOfItem(childItem)) {
4163  TREE_ERR("Cyclic dependency in "
4164  << item->object()->getObject()->getFullName()
4165  << '.' << childItem->object()->getObject()->getFullName());
4166  --i;
4167  continue;
4168  }
4169  it->second->rootItem = nullptr;
4170  childItem->setHighlight(false);
4171  this->removeChild(childItem);
4172  item->insertChild(i, childItem);
4173  assert(childItem->parent() == item);
4174  if (checkHidden)
4175  updateItemsVisibility(childItem, false);
4176  }
4177  }
4178 
4179  for (++i; item->childCount() > i;) {
4180  QTreeWidgetItem* ci = item->child(i);
4181  if (ci->type() == TreeWidget::ObjectType) {
4182  auto childItem = static_cast<DocumentObjectItem*>(ci);
4183  if (childItem->requiredAtRoot()) {
4184  item->removeChild(childItem);
4185  auto index = findRootIndex(childItem->object()->getObject());
4186  if (index >= 0)
4187  this->insertChild(index, childItem);
4188  else
4189  this->addChild(childItem);
4190  assert(childItem->parent() == this);
4191  if (checkHidden)
4192  updateItemsVisibility(childItem, false);
4193  childItem->myData->rootItem = childItem;
4194  continue;
4195  }
4196  }
4197 
4198  bool lock = getTree()->blockSelection(true);
4199  delete ci;
4200  getTree()->blockSelection(lock);
4201  }
4202  if (updated)
4203  getTree()->_updateStatus();
4204 }

4206 int DocumentItem::findRootIndex(App::DocumentObject* childObj) {
4207  if (!TreeParams::getKeepRootOrder() || !childObj || !childObj->isAttachedToDocument())
4208  return -1;
4209 
4210  // Use view provider's tree rank to find correct place at the root level.
4211 
4212  int count = this->childCount();
4213  if (!count)
4214  return -1;
4215 
4216  int first, last;
4217 
4218  auto getTreeRank = [](Gui::ViewProviderDocumentObject* vp) -> int {
4219  if (vp->getTreeRank() == -1) {
4220  vp->setTreeRank(vp->getObject()->getID());
4221  }
4222  return vp->getTreeRank();
4223  };
4224 
4225  auto vpc = dynamic_cast<ViewProviderDocumentObject*>(Application::Instance->getViewProvider(childObj));
4226  int childTreeRank = getTreeRank(vpc);
4227 
4228  // find the last item
4229  for (last = count - 1; last >= 0; --last) {
4230  auto citem = this->child(last);
4231  if (citem->type() == TreeWidget::ObjectType) {
4232  auto vp = static_cast<DocumentObjectItem*>(citem)->object();
4233  if (getTreeRank(vp) <= childTreeRank) {
4234  return last + 1;
4235  }
4236  break;
4237  }
4238  }
4239 
4240  // find the first item
4241  for (first = 0; first < count; ++first) {
4242  auto citem = this->child(first);
4243  if (citem->type() == TreeWidget::ObjectType) {
4244  auto vp = static_cast<DocumentObjectItem*>(citem)->object();
4245  if (getTreeRank(vp) > childTreeRank) {
4246  return first;
4247  }
4248  break;
4249  }
4250  }
4251 
4252  // now do a binary search to find the lower bound, assuming the root level
4253  // object is already in order
4254  count = last - first;
4255  int pos;
4256  while (count > 0) {
4257  int step = count / 2;
4258  pos = first + step;
4259  for (; pos <= last; ++pos) {
4260  auto citem = this->child(pos);
4261  if (citem->type() != TreeWidget::ObjectType)
4262  continue;
4263  auto vp = static_cast<DocumentObjectItem*>(citem)->object();
4264  if (vp->getTreeRank() < childTreeRank) {
4265  first = ++pos;
4266  count -= step + 1;
4267  }
4268  else
4269  count = step;
4270  break;
4271  }
4272  if (pos > last)
4273  return -1;
4274  }
4275  if (first > last)
4276  return -1;
4277  return first;
4278 }

4280 void DocumentItem::sortObjectItems()
4281 {
4282  QSignalBlocker guard(getTree());
4283 
4284  std::vector<DocumentObjectItem*> sortedItems;
4285  sortedItems.reserve(this->childCount());
4286 
4287  for (int i = 0; i < this->childCount(); ++i) {
4288  QTreeWidgetItem* treeItem = this->child(i);
4289  if (treeItem->type() == TreeWidget::ObjectType) {
4290  sortedItems.push_back(static_cast<DocumentObjectItem*>(treeItem));
4291  }
4292  }
4293 
4294  std::stable_sort(sortedItems.begin(), sortedItems.end(),
4295  [](DocumentObjectItem* a, DocumentObjectItem* b) {
4296  return a->object()->getTreeRank() < b->object()->getTreeRank();
4297  });
4298 
4299  int sortedIndex = 0;
4300  std::vector<bool> expansion;
4301  for (int i = 0; i < this->childCount(); ++i) {
4302  QTreeWidgetItem* treeItem = this->child(i);
4303  if (treeItem->type() != TreeWidget::ObjectType) {
4304  continue;
4305  }
4306 
4307  DocumentObjectItem* sortedItem = sortedItems[sortedIndex++];
4308  if (sortedItem == treeItem) {
4309  continue;
4310  }
4311 
4312  expansion.clear();
4313  sortedItem->getExpandedSnapshot(expansion);
4314 
4315  this->removeChild(sortedItem);
4316  this->insertChild(i, sortedItem);
4317  if (!showHidden()) {
4318  updateItemsVisibility(sortedItem, false);
4319  }
4320 
4321  std::vector<bool>::const_iterator expFrom = expansion.cbegin();
4322  sortedItem->applyExpandedSnapshot(expansion, expFrom);
4323  }
4324 }

4562  const Gui::TreeItemMode& mode, const App::DocumentObject* parent, const char* subname)
4563 {
4564  getTree()->_updateStatus(false);
4565 
4566  if ((mode == TreeItemMode::ExpandItem ||
4567  mode == TreeItemMode::ExpandPath) &&
4568  obj.getDocument()->getDocument()->testStatus(App::Document::Restoring)) {
4569  if (!_ExpandInfo)
4570  _ExpandInfo.reset(new ExpandInfo);
4571  _ExpandInfo->emplace(std::string("*") + obj.getObject()->getNameInDocument(), ExpandInfoPtr());
4572  return;
4573  }
4574 
4575  if (parent && parent->getDocument() != document()->getDocument()) {
4576  auto it = getTree()->DocumentMap.find(Application::Instance->getDocument(parent->getDocument()));
4577  if (it != getTree()->DocumentMap.end())
4578  it->second->slotExpandObject(obj, mode, parent, subname);
4579  return;
4580  }
4581 
4582  FOREACH_ITEM(item, obj)
4583  // All document object items must always have a parent, either another
4584  // object item or document item. If not, then there is a bug somewhere
4585  // else.
4586  assert(item->parent());
4587 
4588  switch (mode) {
4589  case TreeItemMode::ExpandPath:
4590  if (!parent) {
4591  QTreeWidgetItem* parentItem = item->parent();
4592  while (parentItem) {
4593  parentItem->setExpanded(true);
4594  parentItem = parentItem->parent();
4595  }
4596  item->setExpanded(true);
4597  break;
4598  }
4599  // fall through
4600  case TreeItemMode::ExpandItem:
4601  if (!parent) {
4602  if (item->parent()->isExpanded())
4603  item->setExpanded(true);
4604  }
4605  else {
4606  App::DocumentObject* topParent = nullptr;
4607  std::ostringstream ss;
4608  item->getSubName(ss, topParent);
4609  if (!topParent) {
4610  if (parent != obj.getObject())
4611  continue;
4612  }
4613  else if (topParent != parent)
4614  continue;
4615  showItem(item, false, true);
4616  item->setExpanded(true);
4617  }
4618  break;
4619  case TreeItemMode::CollapseItem:
4620  item->setExpanded(false);
4621  break;
4622  case TreeItemMode::ToggleItem:
4623  if (item->isExpanded())
4624  item->setExpanded(false);
4625  else
4626  item->setExpanded(true);
4627  break;
4628 
4629  default:
4630  break;
4631  }
4632  if (item->isExpanded())
4633  populateItem(item);
4634  if (parent)
4635  return;
4636  END_FOREACH_ITEM
4637 }

4743 void DocumentItem::updateItemSelection(DocumentObjectItem* item)
4744 {
4745  // Note: In several places of this function the selection is altered and the notification of
4746  // the selection observers can trigger a recreation of all DocumentObjectItem so that the
4747  // passed 'item' can become a dangling pointer.
4748  // Thus,'item' mustn't be accessed any more after altering the selection.
4749  // For further details see the bug analysis of #13107
4750  bool selected = item->isSelected();
4751  bool checked = item->checkState(0) == Qt::Checked;
4752 
4753  if (selected && !checked)
4754  item->setCheckState(true);
4755 
4756  if (!selected && checked)
4757  item->setCheckState(false);
4758 
4759  if ((selected && item->selected > 0) || (!selected && !item->selected)) {
4760  return;
4761  }
4762  if (item->selected != -1)
4763  item->mySubs.clear();
4764  item->selected = selected;
4765 
4766  auto obj = item->object()->getObject();
4767  if (!obj || !obj->isAttachedToDocument())
4768  return;
4769 
4770  std::ostringstream str;
4771  App::DocumentObject* topParent = nullptr;
4772  item->getSubName(str, topParent);
4773  if (topParent) {
4774  if (!obj->redirectSubName(str, topParent, nullptr))
4775  str << obj->getNameInDocument() << '.';
4776  obj = topParent;
4777  }
4778  const char* objname = obj->getNameInDocument();
4779  const char* docname = obj->getDocument()->getName();
4780  const auto& subname = str.str();
4781 
4782 #ifdef FC_DEBUG
4783  if (!subname.empty()) {
4784  assert(item->getParentItem());
4785  }
4786 #endif
4787 
4788  if (!selected) {
4789  Gui::Selection().rmvSelection(docname, objname, subname.c_str());
4790  return;
4791  }
4792 
4793  auto vobj = item->object();
4794  selected = false;
4795  if (!item->mySubs.empty()) {
4796  for (auto& sub : item->mySubs) {
4797  if (Gui::Selection().addSelection(docname, objname, (subname + sub).c_str())) {
4798  selected = true;
4799  }
4800  }
4801  }
4802  if (!selected) {
4803  item->mySubs.clear();
4804  if (!Gui::Selection().addSelection(docname, objname, subname.c_str())) {
4805  // Safely re-access the item
4806  DocumentObjectItem* item2 = findItem(vobj->getObject(), subname);
4807  if (item2) {
4808  item2->selected = 0;
4809  item2->setSelected(false);
4810  item2->setCheckState(false);
4811  }
4812  return;
4813  }
4814  }
4815  getTree()->syncView(vobj);
4816 }

4818 App::DocumentObject* DocumentItem::getTopParent(App::DocumentObject* obj, std::string& subname) {
4819  auto it = ObjectMap.find(obj);
4820  if (it == ObjectMap.end() || it->second->items.empty())
4821  return nullptr;
4822 
4823  // already a top parent
4824  if (it->second->rootItem)
4825  return obj;
4826 
4827  for (auto item : it->second->items) {
4828  // non group object do not provide a coordinate system, hence its
4829  // claimed child is still in the global coordinate space, so the
4830  // child can still be considered a top level object
4831  if (!item->isParentGroup())
4832  return obj;
4833  }
4834 
4835  // If no top level item, find an item that is closest to the top level
4836  std::multimap<int, DocumentObjectItem*> items;
4837  for (auto item : it->second->items) {
4838  int i = 0;
4839  for (auto parent = item->parent(); parent; ++i, parent = parent->parent()) {
4840  if (parent->isHidden())
4841  i += 1000;
4842  ++i;
4843  }
4844  items.emplace(i, item);
4845  }
4846 
4847  App::DocumentObject* topParent = nullptr;
4848  std::ostringstream ss;
4849  items.begin()->second->getSubName(ss, topParent);
4850  if (!topParent) {
4851  // this shouldn't happen
4852  FC_WARN("No top parent for " << obj->getFullName() << '.' << subname);
4853  return obj;
4854  }
4855  ss << obj->getNameInDocument() << '.' << subname;
4856  FC_LOG("Subname correction " << obj->getFullName() << '.' << subname
4857  << " -> " << topParent->getFullName() << '.' << ss.str());
4858  subname = ss.str();
4859  return topParent;
4860 }

4871  return *(it->second->items.begin());

4885

4895 DocumentObjectItem* DocumentItem::findItemByObject(
4896  bool sync, App::DocumentObject* obj, const char* subname, bool select)
4897 {
4898  if (!subname)
4899  subname = "";
4900 
4901  auto it = ObjectMap.find(obj);
4902  if (it == ObjectMap.end() || it->second->items.empty())
4903  return nullptr;
4904 
4905  // prefer top level item of this object
4906  if (it->second->rootItem)
4907  return findItem(sync, it->second->rootItem, subname, select);
4908 
4909  for (auto item : it->second->items) {
4910  // non group object do not provide a coordinate system, hence its
4911  // claimed child is still in the global coordinate space, so the
4912  // child can still be considered a top level object
4913  if (!item->isParentGroup())
4914  return findItem(sync, item, subname, select);
4915  }
4916 
4917  // If no top level item, find an item that is closest to the top level
4918  std::multimap<int, DocumentObjectItem*> items;
4919  for (auto item : it->second->items) {
4920  int i = 0;
4921  for (auto parent = item->parent(); parent; ++i, parent = parent->parent())
4922  ++i;
4923  items.emplace(i, item);
4924  }
4925  for (auto& v : items) {
4926  auto item = findItem(sync, v.second, subname, select);
4927  if (item)
4928  return item;
4929  }
4930  return nullptr;

4933 DocumentObjectItem* DocumentItem::findItem(
4934  bool sync, DocumentObjectItem* item, const char* subname, bool select)
4935 {
4936  if (item->isHidden())
4937  item->setHidden(false);
4938 
4939  if (!subname || *subname == 0) {
4940  if (select) {
4941  item->selected += 2;
4942  item->mySubs.clear();
4943  }
4944  return item;
4945  }
4946 
4947  TREE_TRACE("find next " << subname);
4948 
4949  // try to find the next level object name
4950  const char* nextsub = nullptr;
4951  const char* dot = nullptr;
4952  if ((dot = strchr(subname, '.')))
4953  nextsub = dot + 1;
4954  else {
4955  if (select) {
4956  item->selected += 2;
4957  if (std::find(item->mySubs.begin(), item->mySubs.end(), subname) == item->mySubs.end())
4958  item->mySubs.emplace_back(subname);
4959  }
4960  return item;
4961  }
4962 
4963  std::string name(subname, nextsub - subname);
4964  auto obj = item->object()->getObject();
4965  auto subObj = obj->getSubObject(name.c_str());
4966  if (!subObj || subObj == obj) {
4967  if (!subObj && !getTree()->searchDoc)
4968  TREE_LOG("sub object not found " << item->getName() << '.' << name.c_str());
4969  if (select) {
4970  item->selected += 2;
4971  if (std::find(item->mySubs.begin(), item->mySubs.end(), subname) == item->mySubs.end())
4972  item->mySubs.emplace_back(subname);
4973  }
4974  return item;
4975  }
4976 
4977  if (select)
4978  item->mySubs.clear();
4979 
4980  if (!item->populated && sync) {
4981  //force populate the item
4982  item->populated = true;
4983  populateItem(item, true);
4984  }
4985 
4986  for (int i = 0, count = item->childCount(); i < count; ++i) {
4987  auto ti = item->child(i);
4988  if (!ti || ti->type() != TreeWidget::ObjectType) continue;
4989  auto child = static_cast<DocumentObjectItem*>(ti);
4990 
4991  if (child->object()->getObject() == subObj)
4992  return findItem(sync, child, nextsub, select);
4993  }
4994 
4995  // The sub object is not found. This could happen for geo group, since its
4996  // children may be in more than one hierarchy down.
4997  bool found = false;
4998  DocumentObjectItem* res = nullptr;
4999  auto it = ObjectMap.find(subObj);
5000  if (it != ObjectMap.end()) {
5001  for (auto child : it->second->items) {
5002  if (child->isChildOfItem(item)) {
5003  found = true;
5004  res = findItem(sync, child, nextsub, select);
5005  if (!select)
5006  return res;
5007  }
5008  }
5009  }
5010 
5011  if (select && !found) {
5012  // The sub object is still not found. Maybe it is a non-object sub-element.
5013  // Select the current object instead.
5014  TREE_TRACE("element " << subname << " not found");
5015  item->selected += 2;
5016  if (std::find(item->mySubs.begin(), item->mySubs.end(), subname) == item->mySubs.end())
5017  item->mySubs.emplace_back(subname);
5018  }
5019  return res;
5020 }

5022 void DocumentItem::selectItems(SelectionReason reason) {
5023  const auto& sels = Selection().getSelection(pDocument->getDocument()->getName(), ResolveMode::NoResolve);
5024 
5025  bool sync = (sels.size() > 50 || reason == SR_SELECT) ? false : true;
5026 
5027  for (const auto& sel : sels)
5028  findItemByObject(sync, sel.pObject, sel.SubName, true);
5029 
5030  DocumentObjectItem* newSelect = nullptr;
5031  DocumentObjectItem* oldSelect = nullptr;
5032 
5033  FOREACH_ITEM_ALL(item)
5034  if (item->selected == 1) {
5035  // this means it is the old selection and is not in the current
5036  // selection
5037  item->selected = 0;
5038  item->mySubs.clear();
5039  item->setSelected(false);
5040  item->setCheckState(false);
5041  }
5042  else if (item->selected) {
5043  if (sync) {
5044  if (item->selected == 2 && showItem(item, false, reason == SR_FORCE_EXPAND)) {
5045  // This means newly selected and can auto expand
5046  if (!newSelect)
5047  newSelect = item;
5048  }
5049  if (!newSelect && !oldSelect && !item->isHidden()) {
5050  bool visible = true;
5051  for (auto parent = item->parent(); parent; parent = parent->parent()) {
5052  if (!parent->isExpanded() || parent->isHidden()) {
5053  visible = false;
5054  break;
5055  }
5056  }
5057  if (visible)
5058  oldSelect = item;
5059  }
5060  }
5061  item->selected = 1;
5062  item->setSelected(true);
5063  item->setCheckState(true);
5064  }
5065  END_FOREACH_ITEM;
5066 
5067  if (sync) {
5068  if (!newSelect)
5069  newSelect = oldSelect;
5070  else
5071  getTree()->syncView(newSelect->object());
5072  if (newSelect)
5073  getTree()->scrollToItem(newSelect);
5074  }
5075 }

5096 void DocumentItem::selectAllInstances(const ViewProviderDocumentObject& vpd) {
5097  ViewParentMap parentMap;
5098  auto pObject = vpd.getObject();
5099  if (ObjectMap.find(pObject) == ObjectMap.end())
5100  return;
5101 
5102  bool lock = getTree()->blockSelection(true);
5103 
5104  // We are trying to select all items corresponding to a given view
5105  // provider, i.e. all appearance of the object inside all its parent items
5106  //
5107  // Build a map of object to all its parent
5108  for (auto& v : ObjectMap) {
5109  if (v.second->viewObject == &vpd) continue;
5110  for (auto child : v.second->viewObject->claimChildren()) {
5111  auto vp = getViewProvider(child);
5112  if (!vp) continue;
5113  parentMap[vp].push_back(v.second->viewObject);
5114  }
5115  }
5116 
5117  // now make sure all parent items are populated. In order to do that, we
5118  // need to populate the oldest parent first
5119  populateParents(&vpd, parentMap);
5120 
5121  DocumentObjectItem* first = nullptr;
5122  FOREACH_ITEM(item, vpd);
5123  if (showItem(item, true) && !first)
5124  first = item;
5125  END_FOREACH_ITEM;
5126 
5127  getTree()->blockSelection(lock);
5128  if (first) {
5129  treeWidget()->scrollToItem(first);
5130  updateSelection();
5131  }
5132 }

5570 bool DocumentObjectItem::requiredAtRoot(bool excludeSelf) const {
5571  if (myData->rootItem || object()->getDocument() != getOwnerDocument()->document())
5572  return false;
5573  bool checkMap = true;
5574  for (auto item : myData->items) {
5575  if (excludeSelf && item == this) continue;
5576  auto pi = item->getParentItem();
5577  if (!pi || pi->myData->removeChildrenFromRoot)
5578  return false;
5579  checkMap = false;
5580  }
5581  if (checkMap && myOwner) {
5582  auto it = myOwner->_ParentMap.find(object()->getObject());
5583  if (it != myOwner->_ParentMap.end()) {
5584  // Reaching here means all items of this corresponding object is
5585  // going to be deleted, but the object itself is not deleted and
5586  // still being referred to by some parent item that is not expanded
5587  // yet. So, we force populate at least one item of the parent
5588  // object to make sure that there is at least one corresponding
5589  // item for each object.
5590  //
5591  // PS: practically speaking, it won't hurt much to delete all the
5592  // items, because the item will be auto created once the user
5593  // expand its parent item. It only causes minor problems, such as,
5594  // tree scroll to object command won't work properly.
5595 
5596  for (auto parent : it->second) {
5597  if (getOwnerDocument()->populateObject(parent))
5598  return false;
5599  }
5600  }
5601  }
5602  return true;
5603 }

5716 int DocumentObjectItem::getSubName(std::ostringstream& str, App::DocumentObject*& topParent) const
5717 {
5718  auto parent = getParentItem();
5719  if (!parent)
5720  return NotGroup;
5721  int ret = parent->getSubName(str, topParent);
5722  if (ret != SuperGroup) {
5723  int group = parent->isGroup();
5724  if (group == NotGroup) {
5725  if (ret != PartGroup) {
5726  // Handle this situation,
5727  //
5728  // LinkGroup
5729  // |--PartExtrude
5730  // |--Sketch
5731  //
5732  // This function traverse from top down, so, when seeing a
5733  // non-group object 'PartExtrude', its following children should
5734  // not be grouped, so must reset any previous parents here.
5735  topParent = nullptr;
5736  str.str(""); //reset the current subname
5737  return NotGroup;
5738  }
5739  group = PartGroup;
5740  }
5741  ret = group;
5742  }
5743 
5744  auto obj = parent->object()->getObject();
5745  if (!obj || !obj->isAttachedToDocument()) {
5746  topParent = nullptr;
5747  str.str("");
5748  return NotGroup;
5749  }
5750  if (!topParent)
5751  topParent = obj;
5752  else if (!obj->redirectSubName(str, topParent, object()->getObject()))
5753  str << obj->getNameInDocument() << '.';
5754  return ret;
5755 }
